name: BBCWorld
text:
Scientists predict at least 550 mammal species will be lost this century, during an unprecedented “global emergency”

Humans are almost entirely responsible for the extinction of mammals in recent history, research suggests

[Thread]

https://t.co/N7BPPEoi6h

name: BBCWorld
text:
With every "lost species" we lose part of the Earth's natural history, experts say

But, despite these "grim" projections, experts hope we can save hundreds of species by stepping up conservation efforts

https://t.co/N7BPPEoi6h https://t.co/yihhrbJCHj

name: BBCWorld
text:
A large dataset of fossils provided evidence for the timing and scale of recent extinctions

This allowed scientists to use computer-based simulations to predict extinction rates by the year 2100, based on the current threat status of species

https://t.co/N7BPPEoi6h https://t.co/xgCYeCxtO6

name: BBCWorld
text:
According to these models, the extinctions that have occurred in past centuries only represent the tip of the iceberg, when compared with the extinctions expected in the decades ahead

https://t.co/N7BPPEoi6h https://t.co/2yuXu25pXs

name: BBCWorld
text:
Scientists warn we are entering the sixth mass extinction

Species are disappearing at more than 100 times the natural rate, research shows

Unlike other mass extinctions, caused by volcano eruptions or asteroid collisions we only have ourselves to blame

https://t.co/N7BPPEoi6h
